      <hedline>
        <hl1>No Spike Lee? No Ramones?; Unhappy About Taxis? Give Ferries a Chance</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Christopher Stephens letter on June 30 article holds solution to cab drivers refusing to take passengers on East 79th St anywhere but Wall Street is at hand; notes East River ferry service is about to begin</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''The 'Only to Wall Street' Taxicabs'' (June 30): Residents of East 79th Street are right to complain about cabbies who bend the rules to get more lucrative fares down to Wall Street. But a solution is at hand.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''The 'Only to Wall Street' Taxicabs'' (June 30): Residents of East 79th Street are right to complain about cabbies who bend the rules to get more lucrative fares down to Wall Street. But a solution is at hand.</p>
        <p>Ferry service will soon take these same Wall Street worker bees down the East River at the same cost and faster, leaving the taxis available to others.</p>
        <p>The only pity is that this ferry service has been delayed because of complaints from some of the same community activists who are worried that ferry service will bring the ''wrong'' kind of traffic through their neighborhood.</p>
        <p>CHRISTOPHER STEPHENS  Yorkville</p>
      </block>
